=== Etymology ===
From Middle English ''bere'' from Old English ''bera'' and related to Old English ''brun'' meaning &quot;brown&quot;.

=== Noun ===
'''bear''' (plural: [[bears]])

# large carnivorous mammal, related to the dog and racoon families. Bears have long shaggy hair, very small tails, and flat feet. They like to feed on fruits and insects as well as fish and meat. 
# an animals resembling bears such as koalas and pandas
# an [[investor]] who sells in anticipation of falling prices
# a problem that is very difficult to solve
# slang for large hairy man, partically a gay man.

====Adjective====
'''bear'''
#(''financial'') a market in which prices are falling (compare [[bull]])

