=== Etymology ===
From Middle English ''beren'' meaning &quot;to carry&quot; and &quot;to bring forth&quot;. The Old English root ''beran'' is related to Old High German ''beran'' meaning &quot;to carry&quot, Gothic ''baíran'';, Latin ''ferre'', and Greek ''phrerein''.  These derive from the Proto-Indo European root *bher.

=== Verb ===
